    <Statements>
      <Statement>Know and apply the Remainder Theorem: For a polynomial &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;(&lt;i&gt;x&lt;/i&gt;) and a number &lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt;, the remainder on division by &lt;i&gt;x &amp;ndash; a&lt;/i&gt; is &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;(&lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt;), so &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;(&lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt;) = 0 if and only if (&lt;i&gt;x &amp;ndash; a&lt;/i&gt;) is a factor of &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;(&lt;i&gt;x&lt;/i&gt;).</Statement>
    </Statements>
